text: Krivoglavci is a village in Vogošća municipality, near Sarajevo, Sarajevo Canton, Republic of Bosnia and Herzegovina. ==Population== ===Ethnic composition, 1991 census=== total: 456 *Serbs - 362 (79.38%) *Bosniaks - 61 (13.37%) *"Yugoslavs" - 17 (3.72%) *Croats - 9 (1.97%) *others and unknown - 7 (1.53%) ==History== ==References== *Official results from the book: Ethnic composition of Bosnia-Herzegovina population, by municipalities and settlements, 1991. census, Zavod za statistiku Bosne i Hercegovine - Bilten no.234, Sarajevo 1991. title: Krivoglavci
